<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748e32bc-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s130109"><num value="130109">§ 130109.</num><heading> Records and inspection</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748e32bd-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s130109/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Records</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>The corporation shall keep—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748e32be-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s130109/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> correct and complete records of account; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748e32bf-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s130109/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> minutes of the proceedings of its national conventions and council of administration.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748e32c0-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s130109/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Inspection</inline>.—</heading><content>A member, or an agent or attorney of the member, may inspect the records of the corporation for any proper purpose, at any reasonable time.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id748e32c1-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1373">112 Stat. 1373</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
